✅ Step-by-Step: Access Google Sheets Data via Service Account
🛠️ 1. Create a Google Cloud Project
Go to Google Cloud Console

Create or select a project.

📦 2. Enable the Google Sheets API
In the left menu: APIs & Services > Library

Search for Google Sheets API

Click Enable

👤 3. Create a Service Account + Download Credentials
Go to: IAM & Admin > Service Accounts

Click Create Service Account

Name it (e.g., "Sheets Bot")

Click Create and Continue

(Optional) Assign roles – not needed if you’re only accessing data shared with the service account

Click Done

Now click on the service account → "Keys" tab → Add Key > Create new key

Choose JSON

Download the file (keep it safe, you’ll use this in your code)

🔒 4. Share the Google Sheet with Your Service Account
VERY IMPORTANT!

Open the Google Sheet you want to access

Click Share

Paste the service account’s email (e.g., your-service@project-id.iam.gserviceaccount.com)

Give Viewer or Editor access